## ThreadID.fromBytes() method

fromBytes takes an ID data slice, parses it and returns an ID. For IDV1, the data buffer is in the form: <version><variant><random-number> Please use fromEncoded when parsing a regular ID string, as fromBytes does not expect multibase-encoded data. fromBytes accepts the output of ID.bytes().

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
static fromBytes(data: Uint8Array): ThreadID;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  data | Uint8Array | The input Thread ID bytes. |

<b>Returns:</b>

ThreadID
